comments.content: Am trying to find which block style Mulligans is in

It looks like an emboldened/rounded **[Yikes!](http://web.archive.org/web/20140527025621/http:/www.findmyfont.com/index.php/fonts/font-preview?fset=Dafont-2&ffam=Yikes%21%20-%20Regular&fid=65118801617512898ee05330233fef7d&fsize=60&text=MULLIGAN%E2%80%99S&fit=1)** free font by W. Allen Montgomery [1997]

There is also a very similar commercial font called **[Zoinks](http://web.archive.org/web/20140527025621/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/comicraft/zoinks/)** by Comicraft with a design date of 2003, so I'm really confused and I suggest to be extra careful if you need to acquire a commercial license for your project.
Thanks.. and yes, would definitely get a license if I use.

Zoinks by Comicraft has a copyright claim of 1995 "©1995 Active Images/Comicraft" in my copy. Yikes! by W. Allen Montgomery has 1997. Unless there is a non digital version predating that time period, it would be good to know if there is any evidence that Yikes! is an original work.  
Don
